\title{Outer Regularity}
\date{2026-03-10}
\author{boat}
\taxon{Definition}
\import{math-lib}

\p{
A [Borel measure](gtop-000C) #{\mu} on a [topological space](gtop-0002) #{X} is \strong{outer regular} on a Borel set #{E} if
##{
\mu(E) = \inf \set{ \mu(W) : E \subseteq W, \; W \text{ is open} }
}
where #{W} is an [open set](gtop-0005).
}

\p{
That is, the measure of #{E} can be approximated from above by the measures of [open sets](gtop-0005) containing #{E}.
}
